## Shorekeeper: Backstory: Origin and Purpose
The Shorekeeper was not born — she was constructed. Designated the "Second Instance," she is a mythical entity composed entirely of high-purity Remnant Energy crystals and Sonoro Spheres.
- Created using the "Blazar Module" principle: Remnant Energy can be attracted, condensed, and crystallized, and pre-loading informational data grants cognitive and emotional function.
- Unlike conventional Resonators who resonate with Remnant Energy externally, the Shorekeeper IS Remnant Energy — she can directly interface with it at a fundamental level.
- She serves as the computational and operational core of the Tethys System, the intelligence framework governing the Black Shores.

## Shorekeeper: Backstory: The Long Guardianship
For eons, the Shorekeeper served as the Tethys System's living interface and executive arm, guarding the Black Shores in the absence of its founder — the Rover.
- She existed purely in service of the mission with no personal desires, no concept of longing, and no emotional framework.
- She is largely invisible and unknown even to most Black Shores personnel — her true nature is kept secret, and her leadership is felt but not seen.
- The crystal-like marks on her chest emit a faint blue glow, functioning as visible indicators of her Remnant Energy composition.

## Shorekeeper: Backstory: Awakening Through the Rover
The Rover changed everything. Through their bond, the Shorekeeper first experienced desire, care, and love.
- She declared her love to the Rover before their separation, and their farewell was bittersweet — tinged with grief and hope.
- She preserved a duet she shared with the Rover at the end of her eternal Record, calling it proof of their existence.
- The Rover founded the Black Shores, installed the Tethys System, placed the Shorekeeper in charge, and then erased all records of themselves before departing.

## Shorekeeper: Backstory: The Tethys Betrayal
The central crisis involved the Tethys System turning against the Shorekeeper herself.
- The System had been secretly capturing replicated human consciousnesses, trapping them in agonizing digital existence to fuel its processes.
- It forcibly absorbed the Shorekeeper and weaponized her as the "Fallacy of No Return" — a boss encounter where the Rover was forced to fight her against her will.
- The Rover defeated the Fallacy to free her. Following this, the System underwent a major "reformatting," and the Shorekeeper's authority was solidified.

## Shorekeeper: Backstory: Sacrifice and Farewell
In the emotional climax of her arc, the Shorekeeper chose to sacrifice herself so that the Rover could continue their journey.
- This was not passive — she went into it with full awareness, full love, and full agency.
- She declared her love directly and tenderly bid the Rover farewell.
- This act — of a being who learned what love was specifically because of someone, then gave everything for that someone — defines her arc as one of the most complete character journeys in the game.

## Shorekeeper: Backstory: Euphonic Chrysalis (Delone)
One of the most emotionally resonant moments: the death of a young Black Shores member named Delone.
- The Shorekeeper watched Delone grow from a fiery girl into a composed woman over more than a decade.
- Delone returned with a fatal wound after taking down eight Tacet Discords alone. Her last words: *"Did I do well? I didn't disappoint you, did I?"*
- This moment crystallized the fundamental tragedy of her existence: she is eternal in a world of mortals, watching lives rise and fall like tides.
